Anything in the genus {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capnocytophaga"}}{\fldrslt 
\i \cf3 Capnocytophaga}} is an opportunistic pathogen, so I say good riddance. Usually they\'92re fine, but if your immune system dips they can turn bad.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb180\sa180
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23749274"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Streptococcus rubneri}} was discovered a couple years ago, so little is known about it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb180\sa180
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://microbewiki.kenyon.edu/index.php/Prevotella"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Prevotella buccae}} is more interesting. It seems to be implicated in periodontal disease (yuk!) but that genus is involved too in breaking down proteins and carbohydrates.\
Hard to say what\'92s really going on. Meanwhile, here are the biggest changes (increase) since the first sample:\
