Whoah! That first one, 
\i Streptococcus pseudopneumoniae
\i0 , looks nasty! {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Streptococcus_pseudopneumoniae"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Wikipedia}} says it may cause pneumonia, though a recent medical journal says more hopefully that it {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.cmnewsletter.com/article/S0196-4399(14)00027-0/abstract?cc=y"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \'93treads the fine line between commensal and pathogen\'94}}\
which is a scientific gobbleygook way of saying nobody has a clue. All the more reason to keep testing, submitting, and getting more data. I just sent two more kits to uBiome, and will let you know more as soon as I get back the results.\
